718051f-b.title: Manhattan: Canal Street - Renwick Street
718051f-b.text:
Canal Street, north side, east from Renwick Street
and showfng prominently the N. E. corner thereof. Hud-
son Street is on the right where the truck and W. E.
Tranter sign appear. The low buildings beyond were sub-
secuently demolished and replaced by the triangular 16
story Holland Plasa Building.
Views 2 and 3 are liwited; the former including
several buildings on Renwick Street, and the latter de-
picting Nots. 497 to 503 Canal Street. In the background
appears the Board of Transportation Building, a structure
adjoining the Holland Tunnel entrance.
View 1: Septemher 27, 1927
Views 2,3 March 20, 1932
P. L. Sperr

718060f-a.title: Manhattan: Canal Street - Watts Street
718060f-a.text:
(1)
Canal Street, west side, from Watts Street, at the south end
of Renwick, to Greenwich Street.
September 27, 1927.
P. L. Sperr.
(2)
The same, nearly four years later. The triangular building,
486-490 Canal Street (116-118 Watts Street) has been replaced
by a filling station. Only its west wall has been preserved,
as a protection to the frame buildings immediately behind.
June 30, 1931.
P. L. Sperr.
(3)
The same at a later date. Note absence of former frame houses.
July 27, 1935.
P. L. Sperr.
